radom_result = [[(1, 0.6), (2, 0.7), (2, 0.8), (1, 0.9)], [(1, 0.7), (1, 
    0.7), (1.5, 0.75), (2.5, 0.85)]]
uncertainty_result = [[(1, 0.7), (2, 0.75), (1, 0.85), (1, 0.9), (1, 0.91)],
    [(1, 0.73), (2, 0.75), (3, 0.88)]]
analyser = acebox.get_experiment_analyser(x_axis='cost')
analyser.add_method('random', radom_result)
analyser.add_method('uncertainty', uncertainty_result)
analyser.plot_learning_curves(title='make_classification', std_area=True,
    show=False)
analyser.plot_learning_curves(x_shift=1, title='make_classification',
    std_area=True, show=False)
analyser.plot_learning_curves(title='make_classification', std_area=True,
    start_point=0.6, show=False)
